#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enhancing virtual machine security with AMD SEV-SNP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can enhance the security of your virtual machines with AMD Secure Encrypted Virtualization-Secure Nested Paging (SEV-SNP). The AMD SEV-SNP feature isolates virtual machines from the host system and other VMs, protecting the data and code. This feature encrypts data and ensures that all changes with the code and data in the VM are detected or tracked. Since this isolates VMs, the other VMs or the host machine are not affected with threats."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section explains the steps to enable and use AMD SEV-SNP on your AMD EPYC server with &productname; &productnumber;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "Technology preview for &productname; 15&nbsp;SP6"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "This feature is shipped as a technology preview in &productname; 15 SP6. The necessary packages are not part of the default installation or repositories. These packages are shipped via a confidential compute module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported hardware"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "A system with an AMD EPYC (3rd Gen or newer) is required to run AMD SEV-SNP virtual machines. The BIOS of the AMD machine must provide the necessary options to enable support for confidential computing on the platform."
msgstr ""

