#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing packages and setting up the base system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "The confidential compute module provides replacement packages supporting AMD SEV-SNP. To ensure a maximum of compatibility, these packages are based on the code streams from &productname; &productnumber;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "The three components that need to be replaced are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Linux kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "QEMU Virtual Machine Monitor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "&libvirt; framework"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "To install the replacement packages, run the command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vm_security.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo; <command>zypper install --from SLE-Module-Confidential-Computing-15-SP6-Pool --from SLE-Module-Confidential-Computing-15-SP6-Updates qemu libvirt kernel-coco</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "After replacing the packages, you must set up the system with a configuration change to make the AMD SEV-SNP feature ready to use. The IOMMU on the host side must be configured in non-passthrough mode. This is required to prevent peripheral devices from writing to memory that belongs to an encrypted guest and destroying its data integrity. The default IOMMU configuration in &productname; &productnumber; is <literal>passthrough</literal> mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "To disable the IOMMU configuration in &productname; &productnumber;, open the <filename>/etc/default/grub</filename> file and add <literal>iommu=nopt</literal> to the <varname>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT</varname> variable."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "To update the bootloader configuration, run the command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vm_security.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;; <command>update-bootloader</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "The system is now ready to be restarted with the confidential computing kernel. It is not selected as the default kernel in the bootloader, so ensure to select it in the boot menu."
msgstr ""

